{# /etc/pf.bogons6 — managed by ansible (roles/firewall)
   Host: {{ inventory_hostname }}
   Generated: do not edit by hand.

   IPv6 bogon prefixes per RFC 6890 — addresses that must never appear on
   the public internet as either source or destination. Referenced by the
   `<bogons6>` table in pf.conf and dropped on $ext_if.

   IMPORTANT: `ff00::/8` (all IPv6 multicast) is NOT in this list. Blocking
   outbound multicast breaks Neighbor Solicitation (NDP) and link-local
   service discovery. cr1-de1 had `ff00::/8` here once and lost ~50% of
   outbound flows to NDP cache misses — see issue #25 for the post-mortem
   and project memory `cr1-de1-pf-bogons6-blocks-ndp`. #}
